The paper introduces a new approach to testing the behavior of programs on a corpus of inputs, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The approach uses topological concepts such as simplicial complexes, which are relevant to computational geometry and topology (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses theoretical details and possible applications, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR).
